Hey presto! This speedy Presto Chicken, Bacon and Mushroom Linguine is ready in under
25 minutes. Bacon acts as a cheat's pancetta here, tossed with chicken, mushrooms and
fresh asparagus in a creamy sauce that's perfectly pleasing.

== Linguine ==

Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with 
@salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

== Chicken, Bacon and Vegetables ==

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}, @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}
and @sliced mushrooms{80%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, 
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.
> It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Tenderstem broccoli{150%g} widthways.

Once the chicken and bacon are cooked through, add the garlic and stir-fry
for ~{30%seconds}.

When the pasta has 4 mins left, add the broccoli to the same pan and cook for
the remaining time until tender.

Once the pasta and broccoli are cooked, reserve some of the @reserved pasta water{100%ml},
then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to prevent it
sticking.

== Sauce and Assembly ==

Stir the reserved pasta water, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}
into the chicken pan, simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked pasta, broccoli and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} to the
sauce and gently toss to coat.

Add another splash of water if the sauce is a bit thick. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the chicken, bacon and mushroom linguine between your bowls.

Enjoy!